# Semgrep ignore list for amigatools.
#
# Semgrep's default ignore patterns still apply; this file only adds
# narrowly-targeted exclusions with a documented reason each. It does not
# blanket-exclude a directory or file type -- only specific files where a
# specific rule is a confirmed false positive that can't be suppressed
# inline (Markdown has no comment syntax semgrep recognizes for nosemgrep).
#
# nostr/README.md: triggers the insecure-websocket-scheme rule on literal
# plaintext-scheme text inside shell-usage code blocks (documentation for
# users, not executable code). The client's actual C source (nostr.c) is
# NOT excluded -- every real match there is fixed with an inline
# `nosemgrep:` comment plus a one-line justification (the encrypted scheme
# is the primary, preferred transport; the plaintext one is a documented,
# opt-in transport for local/test relays, chosen only when the caller's
# URL says so).
nostr/README.md
